title: Apple
description: Whilst its ability to keep the medicae away has yet to be proven, this common fruit can be found growing on trees in the summer months and is a staple in the pantry of peasants and noblemen alike.

title: Apple Pie
description: Sweet and comforting.

title: Bacon
description: There is truly no better way to start the day than with a fresh chunk of this salted pork.
notes: Art Description: A chunk of raw bacon

title: Baked Crab
description: The crab flesh is coated in spiced butter before baking in the oven to perfection.

title: Baked Fish
description: A delicious-looking plate of baked, white fish on a bed of vegetables seasoned with freshly squeezed lemon.

title: Baked Mushrooms
description: The nutty flavor of the wyrdloaf mixes wonderfully with the aromas of garlic to produce a meal fit for an emperor.

title: Baked Onions
description: Onions are easily grow, keep for long and go a long ways towards covering up the taste of half-spoiled fish or meat.

title: Baked Oysters
description: Tender oysters coated in bread-crumbs and baked until just right. You just hope the oysters were fresh...

title: Baked Potato
description: It is said that potatoes alone can nourish a man's body indefinitely. The same cannot be said for his soul.

title: Beef
description: A favorite on many a noble’s table, this thick cut of meat is as rich in iron as it is in flavor.
notes: Art Description: A piece of raw venison. Perhaps in the style of a t-bone style steak?

title: Beef Stew
description: A thick, hearty stew of beef cooked in rich, Ombarian wine.

title: Butter
description: Due to its affordability, the rich and creamy, salted butter from Heartlander cows is a popular source of nourishment amongst the lower classes of the Empire. There’s nothing butter.

title: Carrot
description: Abundant and healthy, carrots are a staple in the soups and stews of the north. Also, Hospitallers claim they improve your night-sight.

title: Cheddar
description: Made from cow's milk, this cheese is common and beloved throughout the Imperial heartlands. Perfect for eating with bread and ham.

title: Cheese Plate
description: Ah, the understated elegance of a cheese and fruit plate.

title: Cheese Sandwich
description: For a few short moments, whilst eating a melted cheese sandwich, all is well in the world.

title: Crab
description: Many of the Empire’s citizens will pay a pretty penny to get their hands on this soft, sweet meat. Boiled in salted water and served on white bread with melted butter and squeezed lemon, crab-meat is truly a feast.
notes: Art Description: Crabs! Either a claw or the whole thing. I prefer the whole thing as that’s what we’ve done with the fish.

title: Cream
description: Rich and creamy. Don’t let the cat have it.
notes: Art Description: A small pitcher of cream

title: Cured Ham
description: Tender, savory and long lasting. Cured ham is found in the cellar of every well-to-do merchant and petty noble in the Empire.

title: Dark Bread
description: A piece of the traditional dark and heavy full-grain bread that is eaten throughout the region by farmers and laborers.

title: Dried Meat
description: A favorite amongst adventures, this smoky, preserved meat can last longer than most people’s lives.
notes: Art Description: Jerky style dried meat

title: Eel
description: Due to their abundance in both rivers and oceans, eels are one of the most popular seafoods in the Empire. So popular, in fact, that some citizens have even been known to accept them as payment.
notes: Art Description: I prefer the whole thing as that’s what we’ve done with the fish.

title: Eggs
description: Don't put them all in one basket.

title: Eggs and Bacon
description: The breakfast of titans.

title: Farmer's Omelette
description: A nice farmer's omelette brings to mind the simple comforts of a quaint, rural life.

title: Fish Stew
description: A steaming bowl of fish and vegetable stew. This type of dish is eaten more or less daily by the coast-dwellers of the north. It could do with some salt...

title: Flour
description: One of the greatest of the Gallian Miracles was the turning of deserts into the great rolling wheat fields that now constitute a large portion of the Heartland. From these flows countless tons of grain and rich white flour.
notes: Art description: a sack of flour

title: Fried Steak
description: A meal to put hair on your chest!

title: Garlic
description: Pungent and full of flavor, this herb is most frequently used to enhance a variety of meals.

title: Grilled Leeks
description: Beyond just the taste, leeks go a long way towards adding some color to the drab cuisine of the poor.

title: Honey
description: Sticky and sweet, this ingredient is often used by cooks to sweeten or preserve food, and is a staple in every mead-makers arsenal. It is even said to have curative properties when applied to infected wounds.
notes: Art Description: A honeycomb dripping with honey OR a glass jar of honey

title: Leeks
description: Beyond just the taste, leeks go a long way towards adding some color to the drab cuisine of the poor.

title: Lemons
description: In the north, lemons are almost exclusively found on ships where they serve to protect the sailors from the terrible scurvy that prolonged idleness and sexual abstinence is known to cause.

title: Mashed Potatoes
description: Just the way mothers all over the Empire would make it!

title: Meat Skewers
description: Richly spiced meat roasted on skewers. A popular dish that the Empire imported from its overseas colonies.

title: Morel
description: Morels are mushrooms that make for excellent eating.

title: Mushroom Omelette
description: The mushroom omelette tastes of the forest.

title: Nuts
description: Often added to meat dishes to boost nutrition, these tasty treats can be found growing on various trees and bushes throughout the Empire.
notes: Art Description: A pile of nuts

title: Ombarian Wine
description: Fine wine imported from the vinyards of the Ombaria. Rumors abound of grape harvests failing due to drought in the Heartlands and wine is currently hard to come by.

title: Onions
description: Onions are easily grow, keep for long and go a long ways towards covering up the taste of half-spoiled fish or meat.

title: Oysters
description: This earthy flavored molluscs has been known to increase a person’s desire and sexual stamina. No wonder then that the courtiers and lay nobility of the Heartlands gorge themselves on this delicacy. Just remember to smell them before you eat them.

title: Pear
description: A freshly picked, juicy pear. Eat it fresh, bake it in a pie or make brandy from it!

title: Penny Buns
description: Penny Buns are mushrooms that make for excellent eating.

title: Perklin
description: The humble perklin makes up for its meager size with its abundance. It's often perserved with salt and eaten year round. The smell is an acquired taste.

title: Potatoes
description: It is said that potatoes alone can nourish a man's body indefinitely. The same cannot be said for his soul.

title: Pumpkin
description: A bit watery and tasteless but might work well in a soup or a pie.

title: Pumpkin Pie
description: Nothing says autumn like a nice old slice of pumpkin pie.

title: Ration
description: A trail ration of dried meats, fruits and grains. As sure to filling as it is boring.

title: Redman
description: The tongue and eyes of the redman swells grotesquely once it's pulled from the depth in which it dwells. Despite its apperance, however, its flesh is considered a delicacy when served baked with lemons and vegetables.

title: Roasted Eel
description: Crispy skin and tender meat: The roasted eel is seasoned with garlic and served with potato chips.

title: Salt
description: An empire runs on salt. As the Gallian Empire's preservative and seasoning of choice, it is no wonder that the Salt Merchant's Guild is both rich and very powerful.

title: Salted Fish
description: The fisherman's best friend. Preferably eaten with a mug of ale on the side.

title: Sheep's Milk Cheese
description: As inexpensive and filling as it is smelly. Sheep's milk cheese is a staple in the northern Hinterlands.

title: Snails
description: Despite their slimy appearance, these small creatures are a delicacy amongst nobles and commoners alike and are often eaten with garlic butter or as part of hearty casseroles.
notes: Art Description: A few (or a single) escargot style snails

title: Spices
description: Imported from far away lands at great cost and risk, spices are worth their weight in gold. Aromatic and delicious, they are a precious commodity used by the upper classes to enhance their meals.
notes: Art Description: A pile of spices. Think middle-eastern style spices so reds and oranges.

title: Squid
description: If they’re not filling the bellies of the upper-class, these slippery sea-creatures are being harvested for their ebony coloured ink.
notes: Art Description: Either the tentacles of the whole thing. I prefer the whole thing as that’s what we’ve done with the fish.

title: Steel-Fin
description: Dead fish eyes stare up at you. Steel-Fin is a staple on dinner tables throughout the Outer Isles. It's commonly eaten in hearthy stews with vegetables.

title: Sugar
description: Due to its rarity, this sweet ingredient is usually only found in the kitchens of noble and middle-class households where it is typically used to make glorious pastries and confections.
notes: Art Description: A small bowl of sugar

title: Vegetable Soup
description: A farmer’s feast, often eaten in the fall when root vegetables are abundant.

title: Warberries
description: Rich harvests from the warberry bush is said to portend war. These tart berries are often used to make jams or other preserves in case food should become scarce.

title: Wyrdloaf
description: Wyrdloaf are mushrooms that make for excellent eating.
